, "name": "Dancing on a dream", "description": "Mechanical lantern slides called chromotropes created wondrously complex patterns of light through sliding glass panels and internal gears."}], "recommendations": [], "creator_credit_for_label": "<p>David O. Selznick and United Artists</p>", "creator_credit_for_label_zh_hans": "", "creator_credit_for_label_pa": "", "creator_credit_for_label_hi": "", "headline_credit_for_label": "<p>United States of America, 1945</p>", "headline_credit_for_label_zh_hans": "", "headline_credit_for_label_pa": "", "headline_credit_for_label_hi": "", "title_for_label_zh_hans": "", "title_for_label_pa": "", "title_for_label_hi": "", "title_for_label_override_zh_hans": "", "title_for_label_override_pa": "", "title_for_label_override_hi": "", "description_for_label_zh_hans": "", "description_for_label_pa": "", "description_for_label_hi": "", "description_for_label_override_zh_hans": "", "description_for_label_override_pa": "", "description_for_label_override_hi": "", "description_zh_hans": "", "description_pa": "", "description_hi": "", "description_override_zh_hans": "", "description_override_pa": "", "description_override_hi": ""}, "description": "<p>Alfred Hitchcock hired surrealist artist Salvador Dali to create an architectural sharpness in his dream sequence for psychoanalytic thriller <I>Spellbound</i>. Staring Ingrid Bergman and Gregory Peck, the  sequence likewise employs complex visual patterns to illustrate the main character’s inner workings.</p>"}], "published": true, "shape": null}